  "description": "Wireless telegraphy and early voice radio: spark-gap transmitters (0.5-10 kW, 100-1000 kHz), crystal detectors (galena, carborundum), vacuum tube detectors and oscillators (Fleming valve 1904, de Forest Audion 1906), tuned circuits, antenna systems, and propagation fundamentals. Range: 50-500 km spark-gap, 100-3000 km with vacuum tube transmitters. Enables maritime communication, aviation communication, and broadcast.",
